GLM Model

Quasi-Poisson model since the number of deaths right-skew distributed

hist(hurricane$alldeaths, ylab = "Frequency", xlab = "Number of deaths")

pdf("gender_year.pdf", width = 8, height = 4)

and Var(Y) >> E[Y] (3.80786^{4} > 44.1

We consider the following glm:

\[g(\mu)=\alpha+f_1(\mbox{mf})+f_2(\mbox{year})+f_3(\mbox{min})+f_4(\mbox{elapsedyrs})+f_5(\mbox{wind})+f_6(\mbox{ndam15})\]

where:

\[\mbox{alldeaths} \sim quasiPoisson(\lambda=g^{-1}(X\beta))\] Some considerations: - limited sample size: n=94 - model with 4 predictors and 1 intercept

Theoretical model

We know in advance that the number of deaths depends on the strength of the hurricane (min,pressure,wind), if it touches a populated area (ndam15), and the historical period (year).

MULTIVERSE ANALYSIS

########################################### possible specifications:
combinations_matrix = expand.grid(list(c("min", "sqrt(min)", "log(min)", "poly(min,2)"),
    c("wind", "sqrt(wind)", "log(wind)", "poly(wind,2)"), c("year", "sqrt(year)",
        "log(year)", "poly(year,2)"), c("ndam15", "sqrt(ndam15)", "log(ndam15)",
        "poly(ndam15,2)")))

combinations = apply(combinations_matrix, 1, paste, collapse = "+")
##################### one list of formulas for each comparison of interest:

#######
formulas1 = sapply(combinations, function(cmb) paste0("alldeaths ~ masfem +", cmb))
mod1 = glm(as.formula(formulas1[1]), data = hurricane, family = quasipoisson())
mods1 = lapply(formulas1, function(frml) update(mod1, formula. = as.formula(frml)))

library(jointest)
library(flipscores)
res1 = join_flipscores(mods1, n_flips = 5000, tested_coeffs = c("masfem"), score_type = "standardized",
    seed = 123)
# dipendenze ggplot2 e cowplot 3 argomenti 1: res: results della funzione
# join_flipscores 2: alpha: valore per gli intervalli di confidenza
p <- spec_curve(res1, alpha = 0.05)
# pdf('spec_curve.pdf',width = 8,height = 5)
p

# dev.off()

2 * mean(apply(res1$Tspace, 1, max) > max(summary(res1)$Score))

t_stat_h0 <- apply(res1$Tspace, 1, max)
observed_t <- max(summary(res1)$Score)
ho_t <- ggplot(data = data.frame(t_stat_h0), aes(x = t_stat_h0)) + geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..),
    fill = "lightblue", color = "black", alpha = 0.7) + geom_vline(aes(xintercept = observed_t),
    color = "red", linetype = "dashed", size = 1.2) + geom_text(aes(x = observed_t,
    y = 0.00035, label = paste("Observed S =", observed_t)), color = "red", angle = 90,
    vjust = -0.5, hjust = -0.5, size = 4) + labs(title = "Histogram of Sign-flip test statistic Under H0",
